Anonymous Sun 05 Dec 2021 16:20:43 No.43727635 Report

>>43725311
Yep, it is. I'm never touching that again. I started writing it when I literally couldn't get myself to leave the bed and as such, the isolationist touch and the native thing came from me wanting to distance the characters as far as possible from human society.

Now, writing the last few pages of the followup felt tedious and quite annoying.My writing style has changed, the stories I'd like to write are different ones and having the ability to just have characters talk or switch perspectives somewhat breaks the monotony of text and makes communicating motives so much easier, allowing me to pack more action in less text without endangering suspension of disbelief.

If I have to write 3 paragraphs on why someone thinks someone else feels something to explain that someone else's actions, that's tedious. If I can just switch perspective, that's refreshing not just for me, but the reader too.
But when I do that, I immediatly make that character familiar, no longer weird and alien.

In C&N i could do none of these. The world did not lend itself to further intrusions, although I thought about intrducing other anthros, but the situation just doesn't lend itself to this. It also whould have entailed interpreting from Hiiyeh and Ryan being forced to sit through a lot that would bore a reader.
Besides, I wanted to be done with it and it would have just dragged out the talk Hiiyeh's society more and more. Without explaining that, I can't talk about motives, and without motives, the story remains enigmatic instead of understandable.

Enigmatic is not something i want in fap fiction.
